headline: Trump's antitrust cops are OK with new mergers. Old tech monopolies, not so much.
summary: President Trump's antitrust cops are so far friendlier about mergers than their predecessors, but they are refusing to let up on one prominent priority of the Biden administration: monopoly prosecutions of the nation's best-known tech giants.
